{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nThis is the convergence mechanism itself: reuse plan-review's novelty machinery to stop code review re-nagging carryover findings and to drop novel low-impact findings on UNCHANGED code, while always raising novel findings on newly-changed code.\n\n## What\n- Consume the reader (`latest_code_review_result`) for the current review's typed key to obtain prior SURFACED findings + the prior `deps` map.\n- REUSE unchanged: the novelty SCORING contract (review_kernel/verify.py novelty_model / NOVELTY_SUBANSWERS) and `rising_floor_drop(priority, novelty)` (review_kernel/decide.py).\n- NEW code-review novelty PROMPT + reviewer id: add `code_review_novelty.md` (system resolved with the diff as domain context; surfaced prior findings appended to the instructions as a context block, mirroring plan-review's novelty runner wiring — NOT a {{plan}}/template-var convention) and register a `code-novelty` reviewer id. Register the reused contract at code_review/contracts.py::register_contracts() (import novelty_model from review_kernel.verify), mirroring plan_review/passes.py. The prompt carries the diff as domain context and the surfaced prior findings in the instructions block, binds the reused novelty contract, and adapts cites_prior_location to source-file/line region semantics; exact front-matter field names + reviewer-index registration follow the live reviewer conventions. Only the prompt is new; the contract/predicate are reused.\n- NEW `region_gate.py` defining the region-state vocabulary as constants: `REGION_UNCHANGED = \"unchanged\"`, `REGION_CHANGED = \"changed\"`, `REGION_UNKNOWN = \"unknown\"`. The detector compares each cited file's current sha256 against the prior `deps[path]`: equal -> UNCHANGED; differ -> CHANGED; path absent from deps / multi-location / absence-evidence / moved / renamed / any error -> UNKNOWN.\n- NEW `region_gated_floor`: a finding is dropped iff `rising_floor_drop(...)` is true AND its region is REGION_UNCHANGED. UNKNOWN and CHANGED both raise. Dropped findings move to the verdict `dropped` bucket; drop_reason reuses the existing field, adding the value \"novelty-region\" alongside plan-review's \"novelty\".\n- FAIL-SAFE: wrap the whole reader+hash+gate in try/except; any error resolves affected regions to REGION_UNKNOWN and returns the full unfiltered finding set (no drops), mirroring plan_review/__init__.py _maybe_apply_rising_floor (lines ~201-202) and _score_floor_novelty (lines ~175-176).\n- Carryover (low-novelty) findings: stamp the explicit schema field `carried_from` (a string: the prior run/patchset key), stamped on the finding dict at the decide/novelty seam; the coach step READS carried_from and omits those findings from coaching; they remain surfaced.\n- Wire into BOTH gate paths (local + Gerrit voter). Pass-1 finder stays prior-blind (neutrality); the novelty seam runs only after find+verify. No eval-gated flag.\n\n## Scope\n- src/rebar/llm/code_review/workflow_ops.py (decide + coach seams), new region_gate.py, new code_review_novelty.md reviewer prompt, reuse of review_kernel.\n- Depends on the reader/payload (revenued-thickset-dassie) and, for end-to-end LOCAL integration, on local persistence (paradoxal-balsamic-bubblefish); region_gated_floor unit tests can proceed against a mocked reader.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A code-review novelty reviewer prompt + reviewer id exist and are registered in the reviewer index, binding the reused novelty contract (diff as context, prior findings in the instructions block).\n- [ ] The novelty contract is registered at code_review/contracts.py::register_contracts(); rising_floor_drop is reused unchanged.\n- [ ] region_gate.py defines REGION_UNCHANGED/CHANGED/UNKNOWN constants used by the detector and predicate.\n- [ ] region_gated_floor drops a finding only when novel AND low-priority AND REGION_UNCHANGED; UNKNOWN and CHANGED both raise; dropped findings carry drop_reason \"novelty-region\".\n- [ ] Any reader/hash/compare error returns the full unfiltered finding set (no drops).\n- [ ] Carryover findings are stamped `carried_from` and omitted from coaching, but remain surfaced.\n- [ ] The Pass-1 finder receives no prior findings; only the post-find novelty seam does.\n- [ ] Tests: unchanged-region low-priority novel -> dropped; changed-region novel -> raised; absence/multi-location finding -> UNKNOWN -> raised; carryover -> carried_from + not re-coached; forced reader error -> no drops."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783631133233223001,"uuid":"d9ca4b8b-cabc-47a1-8fd3-4cb5ae4f8a43"}